# OrderFlow — Features (v1)

> **Project:** Distributed order-fulfillment engine. Headline pattern: **Saga
> orchestrator with compensating transactions** (orchestration, not choreography).
> Saga logic lives in **one place**: order-service, as a state machine.
> **Goal:** interview-defensible depth, not breadth.

## Milestone ↔ Workflow mapping

These milestones are **Step 5 delivery slices** (each a STOP-and-evaluate gate).
Planning Steps 0–4.5 lock the *whole system's* contracts up front; milestones then
build it in working, demoable slices.

| Milestone | Slice | Features |
|---|---|---|
| **M1** | order + inventory, 1-step saga + compensation proof | F-01, F-02, F-03, F-04, F-05, F-06, F-07 |
| **M2** | + payment, 2-step saga, cascading rollback | F-08, F-09 |
| **M3** | + shipment, 3-step saga, circuit breaker | F-10, F-11, F-12 |
| **M4** | dashboard + observability + demo | F-13, F-14, F-15, F-16 |

