## Extensible (future — NOT building now)

- **Choreography variant** — contrast doc/branch showing event-driven (no central
  orchestrator) for interview discussion. *Now:* keep saga logic isolated behind an
  orchestrator interface so an alt driver is conceivable.
- **Database-per-service (true isolation)** — split the single Postgres into 4 instances.
  *Now:* per-service schema + per-service DB user so the seam already exists.
- **Saga timeouts / dead-letter + manual intervention queue** for stuck sagas.
  *Now:* persist step timestamps + correlationId so a timeout sweeper can be added.
- **Real payment/carrier integrations** replacing mocks.
- **Auth + multi-tenant** (out of scope for the local demo).
- **Event sourcing** of saga state (currently state + audit log, not full ES).
- **Horizontal scaling / partitioned consumers** with consumer-group rebalancing demo.

